Description: Soplos Linux System Services Manager
 A GTK3 graphical manager for systemd services on Soplos Linux Boro,
 Tyron and Tyson. Provides a clean interface to view, control and
 monitor all system services without using the terminal.
 .
 Features:
  - Complete view of all systemd services (name, state, sub-state, description)
  - Start, stop, restart, enable and disable services
  - Real-time journalctl log viewer for any selected service
  - GNOME, XFCE and KDE (Plasma) support
  - X11 and Wayland compatible
  - Automatic dark/light theme detection per desktop environment
  - 8-language interface (de, en, es, fr, it, pt, ro, ru)
